ssical history. The resulting volume is indispensible for anyone who wishes to appreciate wine to its fullest.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Agriculture & Food (see also POLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Agriculture & Food Policy).2bisacsh1 aDeSalle, Rob, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aWynne, Patricia J.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311067250340uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030021660840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300216608423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300216608/original  a978-3-11-067250-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles